column3: Completed build up of NEW system sn 0033.  Tested all sensor inputs successfully.  RF modem tested okay.  Installed new Iridium SIM card. Successfully tested GPS and XMIT functions with roof-mounted antennas connected inside lab.
Ran Current drain test for  3 days, 15.2 mA Average.  Dumped FLASH RAM data file, which looked okay.
Need to run GPS and XMIT test with system antennas (not roof antennas).
Back from French PIRATA, PI1-18-TH, 10S-10W, PT010. Data okay.
Installed metal SS standoffs at the bottom of the circuit board stack.
Ran Current drain test for  6 days, 13.40 mA Average.  Dumped FLASH RAM data file, which looked okay.
Installed NEW O-rings, face and jam seal.
Successfully tested the GPS and Iridium XMIT outside.
